description:
JOB DETAILS:
Job Purpose
To operate Water Treatment Plants and Booster Stations in a professional manner and ensure water production, distribution and quality targets are met.
Qualifications and/ or skills
• Full Grade twelve (12) School Certificate with at least five (5) ‘O’ level credits including English language and Mathematics;
• Craft Certificate in water supply operations;
• Must provide own accommodation in Solwezi district.
• Member of EIZ

Responsibilities
• Operation of both raw and high lift water pumps;
• Operation and management of flocculators, sedimentation tanks and filters;
• Proper usage and dosing of water treatment chemicals;
• Maintaining relevant plant records;
• Carry out Basic Electrical and Mechanical routine planned and repair maintenance;
• Maintaining working environment in an acceptable state of cleanness and tidiness;
• Handing over plant to relieving operator in a systematic manner;
• Securing plant equipment from damage from preventable causes and from... theft.;
• Carry out any other duties as assigned from time to time by senior officials;
• And other responsibilities that may be assigned by the hierarchy in the interest of the company.

Education Requirement: No Requirements

Job Experience: No Requirements

Work Hours: 8

Experience in Months:

Level of Education

